            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            
                            <p>Letter from a prisoner of war, M Dolan, to Lady Clonbrock (1839-1928). Dolan is writing to inform Lady Clonbrock that he is a resident of Ballinasloe, Galway and asks her to send parcels to him. </p>
                            
                        
                            
                        
                            
                            <p>Augusta Caroline Dillon (n√©e Crofton) was the wife of Luke Gerald Dillon (1834-1917), the 4th Baron of Clonbrock, Co. Galway and the daughter of Lord Crofton of Mote Park (Edward Henry Churchill Crofton, 3rd Baron), Co. Roscommon. Aged 75 at the outbreak of war, Lady Clonbrock, worked closely with the Irish Women's Association to send basic necessities to Irish POWs. Many of her care packages went to members of the Connaught Rangers imprisoned in Limburg near Cologne.</p>
                            
                        
                    
                </note>
